The paper discusses a hybrid memory architecture using DRAM and NVM, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). The proposed scheme is implemented at the operating system level, which suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses the effect of data migrations on performance and power consumption, which falls under the sub-categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), systems and control (cs.SY), and software engineering (cs.SE).
